CSS: (Cascading Style Sheet)
=> It is the Technology
=> it define how the element is to be displayed
=> It save your time
=> it control layout of your web page

CSS:
1. Inline CSS (only use for one)
=> It used within the opening tag/ it uses the style attribute

2. Internal CSS (only one webpage ) 
=> it used within the header(<head></head>)/ it uses the <style> tag and  selector(tagname, ., #, tagname.)

3. External CSS (more than one webpage)
=> file should be saved wih .css etension
=> Head => <link rel="stylesheet" href="filemae.css">

Sytex:

{
	property: value;
	property1: value1;
	property2: value2;
}